Dear Parents â€“Online Registration will begin for Barbara Worth on August 1, 2019 at 10:00 a.m., and for all elementary sites on August 5, 2019 at 1:30 p.m.
Parents will be able to register through their Parent Portal Account. If you require additional assistance, we will have a workshop on Tuesday, July 23rd, 2019 at the Community Learning Center located at 206 D Street from 1:00 p.m. to 4:00 p.m.
Please find user guides at www.besd.org
If you have any additional questions please contact the District Office at (760) 344-2330 ext. 1005.

Classified School Employee Week
Please join me in thanking all of our classified employees as we observe Classified School Employee Week starting May 20th and ending May 26th. All classified employees play a pivotal role in making sure all operations of our school district are seamless. Your contributions to our school district are deeply appreciated.

post_text:
Our 2nd electric bus arrived on April 29th. The cost of each bus was $400,000 and $5,000 for infrastructure. This grant was made possible by the following agencies: North Coast Unified Air Quality Management District, Calif. Climate Investments, & Calif. Air Resource Board.

Thank you, Freddy Cornejo for submitting funding grant application which enabled BESD to receive over $800,000 worth of free money on the acquisition of these two buses. A third electric bus is on its way to Brawley, CA

post_text: We are proud to announce that Executive Assistant Lorraine Sidhu was selected ACSA Region 18 Administrator of the Year in the Confidential Employee category. Mrs. Sidhu is a consummate Executive Assistant and her professionalism, caring demeanor, humbleness, intelligence, and sense of service to the District is valued by all. She has been an excellent ambassador of our school district and an employee who champions the success of our efforts in advancing student learning. Congratulations, Mrs. Sidhu! You will represent our county very well, and the entire Team BESD is very proud of you!

Congratulations to teacher Kristen Castro of Witter School who was selected 2019 â€œTeacher of the Yearâ€ by the Association of California School Administrators- Imperial County Charter. Mrs. Castro exemplifies the personal and professional qualities that characterize outstanding teachers. Her high level of competence in all areas as an Early Reading Intervention teacher and her unwavering commitment to serve her students is unequivocally a reflection of her dedication and passion to her profession.

Brawley Elementary School District Board of Trustees and staff are very proud of you.
